	)
	(text "Here's our power scheme: \n\n- VBUS is the input from the BEC (battery eliminator circuit) of the ESC. It's full of harmonics and is NOT clean at all. \nWe use this to drive servos and NOTHING ELSE. \n- The 12V net is the battery raw input. This is used to power the rest of the flight computer\n- The 5V rail is generated by a TPS54302 switching supply from the 12V rail. \n- The 3.3V net is true 3.3v and is the primary system voltage for the entire flight computer."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 22.86 29.972 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "bc0a75bf-282f-4fd3-af78-024a1951e0f0")
	)
	(text "Supply Indicator"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 135.382 92.71 0)
		(effects
